Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
insert_physical_cell(25.10)                        insert_physical_cell(25.10)

Name
       insert_physical_cell  -  Provides  a  flexible  way to insert and check
       physical cells

Syntax
        insert_physical_cell

       [-help]

       [-cell <string>]

       [-genTemplateOnly <string>]

       [-inputFile <filename>]

       [-insertRowAreaBoundary]

       [-averageWindow | { [-insertNearBoundary  ]  [-box  {<x1  y1  x2  y2>}]
       [-minimalNumberOfTCD <integer>]}]

       [-verifyWindow {<x y>}[ [-verifyOnly ][-xStep <float>] [-yStep <float>]
       ] ]

       Provides  a  flexible way to insert and check physical cells. It can be
       used to assign a specific area for physical insertion, not only the die
       area.

       Note: The insert_physical_cell command is suitable for inserting physi-
       cal cells as a pattern. The class of these cells must be block and  not
       core.  The  insert_physical_cell  command  is not when the class of the
       physical cells is core and there is no requirement for inserting  cells
       in a pattern.

Parameters
       -averageWindow
              When  specified,  it  changes the window calculation approach to
              average. The size of windows for inserting cell is  the  average
              of  the  core box. The insertion will be done not exactly in ac-
              cordance with the size defined in spec file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -box {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specify the bounding box of the physical cell in <x1 y1 x2 y2>.

              For example, the following command inserts the cell DTCDCELL  in
              the (x1 y1 x2 y2) box.

              insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDCELL -inputFile SPECFILE -box {x1
              y1 x2 y2}

              Data_type: box, optional

       -cell <string>
              Specify the physical cell name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -genTemplateOnly <string>
              Generates  a  template file to guide how to define spec file for
              DTCD, ICOVL and LinerCell.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each insert_physical_cell parameter. For a de-
              tailed description of the command and all of its parameters, use
              the man command:

              man insert_physical_cell

       -inputFile <filename>
              Specify the spec file for physical cells.

              Note: The inserted physical cells must be specified  in  a  spec
              file.  This file specifies the information related to the dimen-
              sions and spacing physical cells. The tool will insert  physical
              cells according to these specifications.

              Here is an example of a spec file:

              *************************

              DTCD Cell cell_name

              WinSizeX          # x dimension of DTCD insertion grid box

              WinSizeY          # y dimension of DTCD insertion grid box

              MacroSpacing      # spacing between DTCD cell and macro

              DTCDSpacing       # spacing between DTCD cells

              PlaceBlockSizeX    #  x  dimension  of padded placement blockage
              around DTCD cell

              PlaceBlockSizeY   # y dimension  of  padded  placement  blockage
              around DTCD cell

              RouteBlockSizeX    #  x  dimension  of  padded  routing blockage
              around DTCD cell

              RouteBlockSizeY   #  y  dimension  of  padded  routing  blockage
              around DTCD cell

              End

              *************************

              Data_type: string, optional

       -insertNearBoundary
              Inserts physical cells near boundary.

              Note:  When  the  window  size is not exactly divided by gridbox
              size, you may not get physical cells near boundary.

              For example:

              insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDCELL -inputFile SPECFILE

              insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDcell -inputFile SPECFILE -insert-
              NearBoundary

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -insertRowAreaBoundary
              Inserts LinerCell around row area boundary.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -minimalNumberOfTCD <integer>
              Specifies the the minimal number of DTCD that must be  inserted.
              If  the  current windows size definition (WinSizeX and WinSizeY)
              cannot fit this requirement, the window size is shrunk automati-
              cally.

              Data_type: int, optional

       -verifyOnly
              Only verifies the physical cells to inserted. It does not  actu-
              ally insert them.

              Note:  The -verifyWindow, -xStep, and -yStep parameters are used
              to specify the size of the window to verify.

              For example:

              insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDCELL -inputFile SPECFILE -verify-
              Window 100 100 -xStep 100 -yStep 100 -verifyOnly

               insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDCELL -inputFile SPECFILE  -veri-
              fyWindow 100 100 -xStep 100 -yStep 100

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -verifyWindow {<x y>}
              Specifies the size of window for verifying the physical cells to
              be inserted.

              Data_type: point, optional

       -xStep <float>
              Specifies the x step of the verify window.

              Data_type: float, optional

       -yStep <float>
              Specifies the y step of the verify window.

              Data_type: float, optional

Example
              * The  following command inserts the cell DTCDCELL in the (x1 y1
                x2 y2) box based on the spec specified in the SPECFILE.

                insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDCELL -inputFile  SPECFILE  -box
                {x1 y1 x2 y2}

              * The  following  command only verifies the cell DTCDCELL in the
                grid box. It does not insert the cell.

                insert_physical_cell -cell DTCDCELL -inputFile SPECFILE -veri-
                fyWindow 100 100 -xStep 100 -yStep 100 -verifyOnly

